metadata.name: Desend #14
metadata.description: Artworks presents blockchain transactions in an artistic form. The canvas depicts wallets and the number of tokens. Transactions, of course, go into blocks, and you can find an artistic way to represent blocks on this canvas. As an artistic representation of decentralization - the lines are not always straight, which reminds us of the branches of the blockchain, synchronization and consensus mechanisms.

metadata.name: The Mountain #32
metadata.description:
Hello, I'm Alexandra Michelle, a lover of pristine and wild nature. I want to embark on an artistic journey to capture the diverse beauty of nature through generative art, paying homage to the wonders and beauty that nature has bestowed upon us and aiming to foster a general respect for the natural world.

Snowy mountainous landscapes offer a mesmerizing realm of beauty and inspiration, attracting millions of people each year. These breathtaking views leave a profound impact on the human psyche, with their unique sense of tranquility.

When we set foot in these areas, we take a deep breath, embracing the cool and clear mountain air. The sound of the mountain breeze reaches our ears, spreading an unparalleled sense of serenity. Freshly fallen snow on the trees dazzles our eyes, imprinting an image of the winter landscape in our minds.

In this generative art project, we aim to bring the magic of snowy mountain nature to life. By utilizing artistic techniques and drawing inspiration from nature, we offer you a piece of this awe-inspiring world. Each component of this project is meticulously crafted and defined as an exceptional artwork, characterized by intricate and captivating details. The project also draws from the color palettes of the four seasons, creating unique palettes for each season.

Furthermore, we invite you to acquire a piece of this artwork. By owning a piece of this project, not only will you have it as a part of your home or workspace decor, but you will also support generative art and encourage artists in this field to continue their creative work in portraying wild nature.

Are you ready to embark on a winter journey to the world of snowy mountain nature?
Made with p5.js.

metadata.name: Soft Cell #28
metadata.description:
This work is an homage to relief printmaking. Other artists have explored the kinship between generative art and print using pen plotters and silkscreen. This work attempts to take the concept of a relief print and apply it to a digital canvas.

This art work is produced in layers. For each layer the printing surface or matrix is defined by one set of algorithms. Another set of algorithms then applies the "ink" (imperfectly!) to the matrix. For each layer in turn the matrix is then applied to the canvas.

Press [s] to save a png image of the work.

The work renders at an economical 800x800px. Any edge size may be specified by adding &sz=x to the URL. A print of about 6 inches by 6 inches is recommended, &sz=1800 at 300dpi.

Rust/JS/WASM
Polygon SDF algorithm adapted from Inigo Quilez.

metadata.name: Treasured Rug #178
metadata.description:
A form of concrete poetry depicting a rug.
Typography created by multiple lines of typewriter text.
Features one of five possible character sets.
One of ten possible palettes for text color
90% chance of black paper, or 10% chance of white
10% chance of rare "Wild" character shift, otherwise 45% of either "Loose" or "Tight"
15% chance each of either rare "Narrow" or "Wide" rug otherwise "Standard"
3 styles of paper grain
Differing line gaps
Differing types of skew effect
Differing types of blend effect when characters overlay.

Press S to save in High Resolution

Uses p5.js and scribble.js
@p1x3lboy August 2022

Re-arranging nature to create art is a beautiful, meditative practice. Stone piles like this can be found anywhere there are stones and humans.

Arranged by Hand will be free to all holders of it's sister piece, Arranged by Ocean 24 hours after that piece's release. 24 hours after that remaining editions will be available to purchase.

Both pieces are created using p5.js.

Key 'h' or 'H' for a high resolution rendering.

metadata.name: UFO #76
metadata.description:
Friend or Foe? ... Orb, Hourglass or Donut? .. who knows? 
These 300 reflective UFOs have been discovered beyond the Kuiper Belt.
All are truly unique. with differing patterns, palettes, stroke colors, sizes and levels of brightness.
Each UFO has four different colored lights shining on it to produce the metallic effect.

Keys for Interaction are as follows:
"R" - To change the rotation of your UFO - morphing it into a different shape
"4" - To produce in a higher resolution
"2" - To produce in a high resolution
"1" - To produce in a standard resolution
"S" - To save a JPG image of your UFO in its current state
"P" - To produce a PNG image of your UFO in its current state

Created by P1xelboy January 2023 using p5.js and WEBGL
